Get-AzureRmWebAppPublishingProfile

Gets an Azure Web App publishing profile.

In this Article

Syntax

Get-AzureRmWebAppPublishingProfile [-ResourceGroupName] <String> [-Name] <String> [-OutputFile] <String>
 [[-Format] <String>] [<CommonParameters>]
Get-AzureRmWebAppPublishingProfile [-WebApp] <Site> [-OutputFile] <String> [[-Format] <String>]
 [<CommonParameters>]

Description

The Get-AzureRmWebAppPublishingProfile cmdlet gets an Azure Web App publishing profile.

Examples

1:

PS C:\> Get-AzureRmWebAppSlotPublishingProfile -ResourceGroupName "Default-Web-WestUS" -Name "ContosoWebApp" -Format "Ftp" -OutputFile "C:\Users\contoso\outputfile"

This command gets the publishing profile in Ftp format for Web App ContosoWebApp associated with the resource group Default-Web-WestUS and stores it in the specified output file.

Parameters

-OutputFile

Output File

Type:String
Required:True
Position:2
Default value:None
Accept pipeline input:False
Accept wildcard characters:False
-Format

Format

Type:String
Required:False
Position:3
Default value:None
Accept pipeline input:False
Accept wildcard characters:False
-ResourceGroupName

Resource Group Name

Type:String
Required:True
Position:0
Default value:None
Accept pipeline input:False
Accept wildcard characters:False
-Name

WebApp Name

Type:String
Required:True
Position:1
Default value:None
Accept pipeline input:True (ByPropertyName)
Accept wildcard characters:False
-WebApp

WebApp Object

Type:Site
Required:True
Position:0
Default value:None
Accept pipeline input:True (ByValue)
Accept wildcard characters:False
